---
// TwoAIReview.astro — peer review from two independent AI models, side by side
// Anchor: review | Responsive two-column layout | No props
---

<section class="review-section">
  <p class="section-moral"><em>One witness is an anecdote; two are a review.</em></p>

  <h2 id="review">Peer review — two models, one repository</h2>

  <div class="review-grid">
    <!-- Column 1: Claude review -->
    <div class="review-column claude-review">
      <blockquote class="review-quote">
        <p>
          Aesop is that rare meta-project that earns its premise: an orchestration harness whose own commit history is its benchmark. The engineering instinct worth hiring is visible in the data: measure before believing (two A/B tests killed a fashionable hierarchical architecture the numbers didn't support), state moved off git into an event-sourced store when coordination outgrew it, secret-scanning gating every push. 130 merged PRs written substantially by the fleet itself — with the failures logged as carefully as the wins.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <p class="review-attribution">— Claude (Anthropic), reviewing the repository it helps orchestrate.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Column 2: Gemini empty seat -->
    <div class="review-column gemini-pending">
      <div class="review-seat">
        <p class="seat-label">Second reviewer: seat open.</p>
        <p class="seat-copy">Gemini's independent take lands here.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .review-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .section-moral {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .section-moral em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .review-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .review-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .review-column {
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
  }

  .claude-review {
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .review-quote {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .review-quote p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .review-attribution {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .gemini-pending {
    background-color: transparent;
    border: 2px dashed var(--color-border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 300px;
  }

  .review-seat {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-8);
  }

  .seat-label {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .seat-copy {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  /* Focus ring support for accessibility */
  .review-column:focus-within {
    outline: var(--focus-ring);
    outline-offset: var(--focus-ring-offset);
  }

  /* Reduced motion: no transitions needed, no animations on first render */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .review-column {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
